data.title: Nausea race day
data.content:
Cheese Breakfast bagel and individual entire cream cheese at 8am.
Bag of gold fish, 3 California Mandarins and skinny pop before noon.
drank most of a cold brew coffee from Scotty's at 12pm-12:20pm. 
One Nutella b ready around 12:40.
(1:30) started drinking Gatorade about 1/3 bottle 
At 1:40 started feeling nauseous and resting heart rate was around 85. Felt better after taking off meet jacket. Mouth felt dry.
Felt nauseous in waves, threw up a tiny bit in mouth twice, being cold helped on warm up at 2:35
(3:05pm) Did 2 strides felt okay during (felt stomach a bit) felt worse after.
(3:25) scratched race, felt a little better after Coach said unpleasant stuff. Got significantly better after staying still. Heart rate came down to 58 after 10 minutes.
Occasional stomach pain, nausea, and mouth watering every so often (4pm). Staying still helps but, doesn't solve the issue. Got electrolytes mix from veyd, drank half a bottle.

(4:05) using core seems to make it a little worse
(5:00) no more nausea, just stomach pain
(5:07) banna
(5:37) stomach stopped hurting 
(6:22) slight nausea after getting on the bus
(8:53) stomach still hurts a bit
